WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.966 --> 00:00:09.593
[sad music playing]

2
00:00:10.886 --> 00:00:13.013
[Ali] No. Mom. We can do better than this.

3
00:00:13.096 --> 00:00:15.849
[Marley] It's going underground.
what's the difference?

4
00:00:15.933 --> 00:00:17.726
[Ali] He would've wanted something nicer.

5
00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:20.229
Well. he should have thought
about that before he left us.

6
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.281
Lilies are a classic option.

7
00:00:31.365 --> 00:00:34.785
Some prefer something
more exotic. like an orchid.

8
00:00:35.285 --> 00:00:39.164
You can also spring for
a custom arrangement for the wreath.

9
00:00:39.248 --> 00:00:41.667
We have an agreement
with the florist down the street.

10
00:00:42.251 --> 00:00:46.255
They will work with you if you have
a design or color scheme in mind.

11
00:00:46.338 --> 00:00:48.340
[sad music continues]

12
00:01:02.563 --> 00:01:05.190
[Marley] Your father and I
weren't big on parties.

13
00:01:05.274 --> 00:01:06.650
[Ali] He only gets one of these.

14
00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:10.362
[Marley] Well. I just don't see
why it has to be such a big to-do.

15
00:01:10.445 --> 00:01:13.740
[Ali] We hired caterers. Mom.
You don't have to actually do anything.

16
00:01:13.824 --> 00:01:17.619
Having help is always more work.
They don't know where anything is.

17
00:01:17.703 --> 00:01:20.455
- There's never enough food.
- There'll be plenty of food.

18
00:01:21.748 --> 00:01:24.585
[sighs] This house isn't big enough
for so many people.

19
00:01:24.668 --> 00:01:26.670
Well. Mel offered to host.

20
00:01:26.753 --> 00:01:28.338
And how would that look?

21
00:01:58.744 --> 00:01:59.745
Dad?

22
00:02:20.307 --> 00:02:22.684
[theme song playing]

23
00:02:25.437 --> 00:02:30.150
♪ A paper shadow in a house of stone ♪

24
00:02:30.901 --> 00:02:35.948
♪ The wooden flag
Of a drifting dreamboat ♪

25
00:02:36.031 --> 00:02:40.160
♪ I never knew
How far the ride was gonna go ♪

26
00:02:40.244 --> 00:02:43.705
♪ Till I looked back at the smoke ♪

27
00:02:43.789 --> 00:02:48.252
♪ You can't keep up with the Joneses ♪

28
00:02:49.044 --> 00:02:53.882
♪ Don't wanna run for the roses ♪

29
00:02:53.966 --> 00:02:59.137
♪ I got my pocket of posies ♪

30
00:02:59.221 --> 00:03:01.723
♪ Sometimes I wonder why ♪

31
00:03:01.807 --> 00:03:03.851
♪ Sometimes I wonder why ♪

32
00:03:04.351 --> 00:03:08.939
♪ I just don't run with the Joneses ♪

33
00:03:09.565 --> 00:03:14.611
♪ Don't wanna smell the dying roses ♪

34
00:03:14.695 --> 00:03:19.700
♪ I got my pocket full of posies ♪

35
00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:24.746
♪ I don't keep up with the Joneses ♪

36
00:03:39.261 --> 00:03:41.513
[inhales deeply. sighs]

37
00:03:41.597 --> 00:03:44.266
[pastor] As we prepare to commit
our brother. Ronald Cooper.

38
00:03:44.349 --> 00:03:46.351
to his final resting place.

39
00:03:46.435 --> 00:03:50.939
I'd like to invite his daughter. Allison.
to honor her father with a song.

40
00:03:54.902 --> 00:03:57.029
[breathes sharply. sniffles]

41
00:03:57.112 --> 00:03:59.489
I used to play this song
when I was younger. [sniffles]

42
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:01.742
And it meant a lot to me.

43
00:04:02.993 --> 00:04:05.120
I'd like to think
it meant a lot to him too.

44
00:04:05.204 --> 00:04:07.581
[playing "Keep Me In Your Heart"]

45
00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:16.005
♪ Shadows are fallin'
And I'm runnin' out of breath ♪

46
00:04:17.007 --> 00:04:20.010
♪ Keep me in your heart for a while ♪

47
00:04:22.221 --> 00:04:27.559
♪ If I leave you it doesn't mean
I love you any less ♪

48
00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:31.647
♪ Keep me in your heart for a while ♪

49
00:04:33.357 --> 00:04:38.904
♪ When you wake up in the mornin'
And you see that crazy sun ♪

50
00:04:39.821 --> 00:04:42.908
♪ Keep me in your heart for a while ♪

51
00:04:44.701 --> 00:04:49.915
♪ There's a train leavin' nightly called
"When All is Said and Done" ♪

52
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:54.044
♪ Keep me in your heart for a while ♪

53
00:04:55.629 --> 00:05:01.510
♪ Lo-lo-lo-lo-lo-lo-lo-lo-lo
Lo-lo-love ♪

54
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:05.097
♪ Keep me in your heart for a while ♪

55
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:07.724
♪ Lo-lo-lo… ♪

56
00:05:07.808 --> 00:05:09.268
[Coop] This is what happens.

57
00:05:10.102 --> 00:05:12.437
You marry your high school sweetheart.

58
00:05:13.021 --> 00:05:14.606
You have a couple kids.

59
00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:16.441
You start making money.

60
00:05:17.192 --> 00:05:18.402
It's not a lot.

61
00:05:18.986 --> 00:05:21.864
but if you keep your nut small.
you can save for a rainy day.

62
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:25.951
And those do come.

63
00:05:27.119 --> 00:05:30.080
So. you tell yourself
next year is the year you'll travel.

64
00:05:30.873 --> 00:05:31.874
buy the nice car.

65
00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:35.669
You get so accustomed
to postponing the reward.

66
00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:38.172
you forget what it was
you wanted in the first place.

67
00:05:39.214 --> 00:05:40.424
But that's all right.

68
00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:43.343
At least you have your health.

69
00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:46.680
Then. on a day like any other day.

70
00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:50.100
you go to sleep. and you don't wake up.

71
00:05:51.602 --> 00:05:54.062
And your carefully managed life
ends just like that.

72
00:05:55.189 --> 00:05:56.273
with no warning

73
00:05:57.316 --> 00:05:58.442
and no fanfare.

74
00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:02.487
Laid to rest by a pastor
who's never even met you.

75
00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:06.325
And knowing my father.
he would have been okay with that.

76
00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:09.328
But I think he would've liked
to say goodbye.

77
00:06:10.454 --> 00:06:11.872
[song ends]

78
00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:14.499
[person] Andrew.

79
00:06:16.293 --> 00:06:19.254
- I am so sorry for your loss.
- Oh. my goodness. Thank you so much.

80
00:06:19.338 --> 00:06:21.840
- Thanks for being here. Appreciate it.
- Yeah.

81
00:06:31.808 --> 00:06:33.060
[sighs]

82
00:06:38.941 --> 00:06:40.943
[chattering]

83
00:06:45.113 --> 00:06:47.449
I kinda always hoped
she'd die first. you know?

84
00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:51.912
Let Dad have a few years to enjoy himself.

85
00:06:52.663 --> 00:06:55.541
[Coop] Yeah. well. she never seemed
terribly happy about being alive.

86
00:06:57.501 --> 00:06:58.961
What about you? You gonna be okay today?

87
00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:01.880
Who. me? Oh. yeah. Why wouldn't I be?

88
00:07:02.631 --> 00:07:04.591
[Coop] It's okay if you're not.

89
00:07:04.675 --> 00:07:06.635
Thanks. But you don't have
to worry about me.

90
00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:08.387
[inhales sharply] I'm sad…

91
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.305
[exhales sharply]
…but in the dead dad way.

92
00:07:10.389 --> 00:07:12.057
Not the bipolar way.

93
00:07:13.267 --> 00:07:14.434
Hey. Mel.

94
00:07:14.518 --> 00:07:16.979
- You sang beautifully.
- [Ali] Thank you.

95
00:07:18.272 --> 00:07:20.649
- And thanks for helping us out.
- Oh. yeah.

96
00:07:20.732 --> 00:07:24.069
Your mom made me add and remove
the leaf to that table like four times.

97
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:25.779
- [scoffs] God.
- [Coop] Sorry.

98
00:07:26.488 --> 00:07:29.199
- Will you take these upstairs. dear?
- [Mel] Oh. Of course.

99
00:07:29.283 --> 00:07:30.868
- [Ali] Mom.
- [Mel] It's… It's fine.

100
00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:33.203
- I'm happy to help.
- [chuckles] Good. I'm glad.

101
00:07:33.287 --> 00:07:36.248
- because the caterer needs it.
- [Ali] Oh. she really doesn't.

102
00:07:36.331 --> 00:07:39.001
[Marley] She doesn't even know
how to use a vegetable peeler.

103
00:07:39.084 --> 00:07:41.420
[Ali] She knows how to prepare food. Mom.
She does it for a living.

104
00:07:41.503 --> 00:07:43.046
- Ali.
- [Mel] It's not a problem.

105
00:07:43.130 --> 00:07:47.009
I will drop these off and then go figure
out the whole peeler/non-peeler situation.

106
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:48.719
Why don't you let me take those upstairs?

107
00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:50.846
- It's okay. I got it.
- [Coop] I can take 'em up.

108
00:07:50.929 --> 00:07:53.932
Why don't you get yourself a drink
'cause I think you could use one?

109
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:01.106
[Coop] What?

110
00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:03.609
You two don't behave
like a divorced couple.

111
00:08:03.692 --> 00:08:04.943
- [Coop] Mom…
- You don't.

112
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:16.413
[guest] We're so sorry for your loss.

113
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:19.750
He loved you so much. It's been ages.

114
00:08:20.959 --> 00:08:23.295
Honey. look at you.

115
00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:25.380
[chuckles] You are a woman.

116
00:08:25.464 --> 00:08:26.757
- [chuckles]
- Isn't she. Glen?

117
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:28.967
Am I allowed to say?

118
00:08:29.051 --> 00:08:30.302
And you.

119
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:33.472
You are the spitting image
of your father at the same age.

120
00:08:33.554 --> 00:08:35.682
[chuckles] You still doing the acting?

121
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:38.684
- Music.
- Right.

122
00:08:38.769 --> 00:08:42.147
You know. my sister's brother-in-law
was off-Broadway once.

123
00:08:42.231 --> 00:08:43.482
I should connect you two.

124
00:08:43.565 --> 00:08:45.734
Again. not acting. [chuckles]

125
00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:47.486
I think they sang too.

126
00:08:47.569 --> 00:08:48.987
Didn't they sing. Glen?

127
00:08:50.822 --> 00:08:52.324
Oh. there's Marley.

128
00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:57.913
[stammers] Well. I'm sorry
about your grandpa.

129
00:08:57.996 --> 00:08:58.997
Thank you.

130
00:09:03.293 --> 00:09:06.338
[exhales sharply] How long
do you think we have to stay?

131
00:09:06.421 --> 00:09:07.923
Oh. I think the whole time.

132
00:09:08.006 --> 00:09:09.299
[sighs]

133
00:09:10.676 --> 00:09:12.761
Oh. God. Mom keeps staring at me.

134
00:09:12.845 --> 00:09:15.013
I can feel how badly
she wants to lecture me.

135
00:09:15.097 --> 00:09:17.057
Okay. don't be a dick to her today.

136
00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:18.517
You're taking her side?

137
00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:21.478
I'm taking the side
of whoever's not being a dick.

138
00:09:25.399 --> 00:09:27.109
[guest] Best trips I've ever taken!

139
00:09:27.192 --> 00:09:30.279
We went in October. December and March.

140
00:09:30.362 --> 00:09:32.197
[Coop] That is a lot of cruises.

141
00:09:32.281 --> 00:09:34.741
- [chuckles]
- Mar… Marley should come this year.

142
00:09:34.825 --> 00:09:36.118
She'll have a blast.

143
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:37.786
Well. good luck getting her on a boat.

144
00:09:37.870 --> 00:09:43.584
I'm telling you. the singles scene
on these things pu-puts Florida to shame.

145
00:09:43.667 --> 00:09:45.085
- [Coop] Is that so?
- Yeah.

146
00:09:46.962 --> 00:09:50.299
- [Ali] Oh. wow.
- So we worked together for over 20 years.

147
00:09:50.382 --> 00:09:52.384
and we did a Secret Santa

148
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:54.928
every Christmas.

149
00:09:55.012 --> 00:09:57.014
[chuckles] We had a running gag

150
00:09:57.639 --> 00:10:02.060
where no matter who got Ron.
they'd give him socks. [chuckles]

151
00:10:02.144 --> 00:10:04.104
[chuckles] I don't… I don't get it.

152
00:10:04.188 --> 00:10:06.815
Was it the socks?
Did they say something funny?

153
00:10:06.899 --> 00:10:09.610
[stammers] No. [chuckles]
It was just a running gag.

154
00:10:09.693 --> 00:10:10.694
[chuckling] Oh.

155
00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:13.071
Ron was always a good sport about it.

156
00:10:13.155 --> 00:10:14.364
[chuckles]

157
00:10:17.743 --> 00:10:22.372
Andrew. Linda Marshall.
I play canasta with your mother.

158
00:10:22.456 --> 00:10:24.249
I'm so sorry for your loss.

159
00:10:24.333 --> 00:10:25.334
Thank you.

160
00:10:26.043 --> 00:10:29.046
The Lord takes us when He takes us.

161
00:10:30.339 --> 00:10:32.132
That is literally true.

162
00:10:36.136 --> 00:10:37.804
You make such a lovely couple.

163
00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:40.807
Oh. you're sweet.
but we've been divorced some time now.

164
00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:42.100
Well… [chuckles]

165
00:10:42.851 --> 00:10:45.521
…my daughter Emily is divorced.

166
00:10:46.480 --> 00:10:47.981
I'll get you her number.

167
00:10:50.192 --> 00:10:52.277
- Okay.
- [Ali] Who's that?

168
00:10:52.361 --> 00:10:55.614
That's Hal Singer. Artie Stein.

169
00:10:56.281 --> 00:10:59.660
and that's me over there looking like
I don't know my ass from my elbow.

170
00:10:59.743 --> 00:11:00.911
Which one is my dad?

171
00:11:01.787 --> 00:11:03.580
He wasn't there that day.

172
00:11:03.664 --> 00:11:05.040
[sad music playing]

173
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:12.673
[Marley] …again and again.
but they just ignored me.

174
00:11:16.760 --> 00:11:17.970
[Coop] Hey. you okay?

175
00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.348
[inhales sharply] Yeah. I just miss him.

176
00:11:21.974 --> 00:11:23.600
[Coop] You wanna step outside
and get some fresh air?

177
00:11:23.684 --> 00:11:25.060
No. no. no. I'm fine.

178
00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:27.938
You need to tap out of this anytime.
just tell me.

179
00:11:28.021 --> 00:11:29.690
- No questions asked.
- [Ali] Thanks.

180
00:11:29.773 --> 00:11:32.192
S-Same goes for you. [inhales sharply]

181
00:11:34.152 --> 00:11:35.445
[exhales sharply] Coop.

182
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:38.574
- Hey. buddy.
- [Grace] Sorry we're late.

183
00:11:38.657 --> 00:11:40.242
Yeah. we had to. uh. make a stop.

184
00:11:40.868 --> 00:11:42.202
I threw up on his shoes.

185
00:11:42.286 --> 00:11:46.582
Oh. well. uh… [chuckles]
…does that mean you're hungry?

186
00:11:46.665 --> 00:11:48.166
Maybe a drink?

187
00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:49.501
[grunts]

188
00:11:54.590 --> 00:11:55.674
[Mel] Oh. Ali.

189
00:11:56.175 --> 00:11:57.426
[Ali] Uh. I just need a minute.

190
00:11:57.509 --> 00:11:59.011
[Mel] Hey. come here.

191
00:12:00.512 --> 00:12:01.847
What happened?

192
00:12:02.764 --> 00:12:04.349
My father died.

193
00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:07.227
I really don't want a scene today.

194
00:12:07.311 --> 00:12:09.313
Oh. my God. Mom. I am not making a scene.

195
00:12:09.396 --> 00:12:10.898
You take your pills this morning?

196
00:12:10.981 --> 00:12:13.317
- Jesus. Mom.
- I'm just saying.

197
00:12:13.400 --> 00:12:14.860
[Ali exhales sharply]

198
00:12:18.113 --> 00:12:19.323
How are you holding up?

199
00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:23.744
Well. I'll be doing better
when all these people are gone.

200
00:12:23.827 --> 00:12:25.537
Is that a smudge?

201
00:12:26.288 --> 00:12:27.623
Maybe.

202
00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:29.124
- [sighs]
- Here.

203
00:12:30.209 --> 00:12:34.671
[exhales deeply] So. Nick is on TV now.
hmm? How's that going?

204
00:12:34.755 --> 00:12:37.424
Oh. you know. we stopped
seeing each other a while ago.

205
00:12:38.050 --> 00:12:39.051
Huh.

206
00:12:39.593 --> 00:12:41.803
- [exhales sharply]
- You feeling all right. dear?

207
00:12:43.180 --> 00:12:44.598
[whispering] Hot flash.

208
00:12:55.984 --> 00:12:58.195
Hold this on the back of your neck.

209
00:12:59.655 --> 00:13:01.490
- [exhales sharply]
- Thank you.

210
00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:03.742
Women die twice.

211
00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:06.161
God forbid we complain about it.

212
00:13:06.245 --> 00:13:08.080
[Ali] Excuse me. Thank you.

213
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:11.750
- [Tori] You okay?
- Yeah. yeah.

214
00:13:11.834 --> 00:13:14.586
if I stay down here. I'll just kill my mom
in front of all her guests.

215
00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:17.339
And then we'll have to come back here
and do this all again next week.

216
00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:19.049
[Tori] Hang on. I'll go with you.

217
00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:24.847
How's she doing?

218
00:13:24.930 --> 00:13:26.014
Which one?

219
00:13:26.849 --> 00:13:28.267
- Exactly.
- [Ashe] Hey. Coop.

220
00:13:29.893 --> 00:13:31.770
- Hey. brother.
- Hey… Oh. oh.

221
00:13:32.437 --> 00:13:34.022
I'm so sorry.

222
00:13:34.106 --> 00:13:36.567
- [Coop] Thank you.
- I brought you some Yamazaki.

223
00:13:36.650 --> 00:13:38.026
[Hunter] Thanks for coming.

224
00:13:38.110 --> 00:13:40.028
You didn't have to come.

225
00:13:40.112 --> 00:13:42.281
- [Ashe] Are you kidding? Of course I did.
- [Hunter] Wanna go upstairs?

226
00:13:42.364 --> 00:13:45.367
Times like these. you…
you shouldn't be alone.

227
00:13:47.035 --> 00:13:48.245
Right. Well. uh…

228
00:13:49.997 --> 00:13:51.832
things are moving ahead
with Bailey Russell.

229
00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:53.876
We should have
the final paperwork next week.

230
00:13:53.959 --> 00:13:56.003
[Ashe] Oh. we don't have to talk
about that right now.

231
00:13:56.837 --> 00:13:58.255
What else are we going to talk about?

232
00:13:58.338 --> 00:14:01.675
Andy. do you wanna keep
your father's hedge clippers?

233
00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:03.844
If not. I'm gonna give them to Neil.

234
00:14:05.053 --> 00:14:06.430
Neil can have them.

235
00:14:06.513 --> 00:14:08.765
[Marley] And when you get a chance.
I'd appreciate it

236
00:14:08.849 --> 00:14:11.560
if you would get that television set
off the living room wall.

237
00:14:11.643 --> 00:14:15.022
- It's an eyesore.
- Maybe not today. Mom.

238
00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:18.817
Well. when's the next time I'm gonna
have a house full of strong backs?

239
00:14:18.901 --> 00:14:20.527
- You must be Mrs. Cooper.
- Mmm.

240
00:14:20.611 --> 00:14:23.030
Hi. I'm Owen Ashe.
A very close friend of your son's.

241
00:14:23.113 --> 00:14:25.824
- I'm so sorry for your loss.
- [Marley] Oh. thank you. dear.

242
00:14:25.908 --> 00:14:27.993
I lost my wife. uh. a few years back.

243
00:14:28.076 --> 00:14:29.453
Oh. I'm so sorry.

244
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.371
Oh… [stammers]
…I'm not gonna sugarcoat it.

245
00:14:31.455 --> 00:14:33.373
- Grief is a motherfucker.
- Oh.

246
00:14:33.457 --> 00:14:35.542
[Ashe] The day of her funeral.
it hadn't hit me yet.

247
00:14:35.626 --> 00:14:39.963
So. I kept looking at the door. thinking
that she was just gonna come walking in.

248
00:14:40.047 --> 00:14:42.424
It was her house… [chuckles] …after all.

249
00:14:42.508 --> 00:14:44.092
Yeah. you have your good moments.

250
00:14:44.176 --> 00:14:46.720
and that makes the bad moments
land a little harder.

251
00:14:46.803 --> 00:14:49.264
But. look. you got a wonderful family
and they love and support you.

252
00:14:49.348 --> 00:14:51.308
- You-You'll be okay.
- Mmm.

253
00:14:51.391 --> 00:14:52.392
Oh.

254
00:14:54.853 --> 00:14:55.979
[Tori] How old is that?

255
00:14:56.063 --> 00:14:57.606
- [Ali] Mmm. I don't know.
- [lighter strikes]

256
00:14:57.689 --> 00:14:59.900
Pot doesn't expire. It's organic.

257
00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:01.735
I don't think that's true.

258
00:15:04.863 --> 00:15:06.240
[blows] It's good enough.

259
00:15:06.323 --> 00:15:08.283
[sighs] What'd she do this time?

260
00:15:09.117 --> 00:15:12.538
Well. apparently. everyone is allowed
to be sad except for me.

261
00:15:14.915 --> 00:15:18.752
I can't even cry at my dad's funeral
without her wanting to lobotomize me.

262
00:15:19.753 --> 00:15:21.922
I think she blames me for his death.

263
00:15:22.923 --> 00:15:24.132
Why?

264
00:15:24.216 --> 00:15:25.884
He was always worried about me.

265
00:15:25.968 --> 00:15:28.220
[clears throat]
I didn't make it easy on him.

266
00:15:29.680 --> 00:15:30.764
He loved you.

267
00:15:32.057 --> 00:15:34.518
Yeah. I guess… [inhales deeply]

268
00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:38.605
I don't like the idea that he was stressed
out his entire life because of me.

269
00:15:38.689 --> 00:15:41.733
Please. She stressed him out
way more than you did.

270
00:15:43.443 --> 00:15:44.820
[sighs]

271
00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:47.739
You know. being the family fuckup
isn't all it's cracked up to be.

272
00:15:48.532 --> 00:15:50.701
Being the golden child isn't any better.

273
00:15:51.535 --> 00:15:53.453
[sighs] Sorry. Not to make it about me.

274
00:15:53.537 --> 00:15:55.289
No. no. Please.

275
00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:56.456
Say more.

276
00:15:57.416 --> 00:15:58.709
I don't know. [sighs]

277
00:15:59.543 --> 00:16:01.795
I guess I should've started
fucking up way sooner.

278
00:16:01.879 --> 00:16:03.463
Yeah. that would've helped.

279
00:16:04.923 --> 00:16:08.760
Do you ever wonder how easier
life would be if we were boys?

280
00:16:08.844 --> 00:16:10.387
[sighs] And. like. mid.

281
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:13.640
Yeah. just two totally unremarkable dudes.

282
00:16:13.724 --> 00:16:15.309
- We'd skate by.
- [blows]

283
00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:21.190
Is that weed?

284
00:16:22.649 --> 00:16:23.650
[blows]

285
00:16:26.153 --> 00:16:29.656
[Nick] Man. when my dad died.
I think I was in shock for. like. a month.

286
00:16:29.740 --> 00:16:32.159
- I guess I thought he'd live forever.
- Yeah.

287
00:16:32.242 --> 00:16:34.620
Never thought I'd be that shocked again.

288
00:16:35.370 --> 00:16:38.999
[inhales sharply] Then came Athens.
[chuckles] Nobody saw it coming.

289
00:16:39.082 --> 00:16:42.002
Heart still breaks every time
I look at that bronze medal.

290
00:16:42.794 --> 00:16:43.962
[Coop] All right. Okay.

291
00:16:44.046 --> 00:16:45.964
I guess I'm saying it gets better. man.

292
00:16:47.174 --> 00:16:48.425
But it also gets worse.

293
00:16:50.093 --> 00:16:51.845
Thank you for that.

294
00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:53.847
[Nick] No. Anytime.

295
00:16:54.723 --> 00:16:57.267
When I die. I wanna be cremated.
No question.

296
00:16:57.351 --> 00:16:59.937
I just don't get why anybody
would wanna be burned like trash.

297
00:17:00.020 --> 00:17:02.356
Well. I'd rather be burned
than eaten by worms.

298
00:17:02.439 --> 00:17:05.233
Plus. there's this thing now where
they can turn your remains into a diamond.

299
00:17:05.317 --> 00:17:07.194
- [scoffs]
- Mmm.

300
00:17:07.277 --> 00:17:08.904
[guest] You'd just be
carrying out my wishes.

301
00:17:08.987 --> 00:17:11.656
- Still. I couldn't.
- [chuckles] I could.

302
00:17:11.740 --> 00:17:15.160
If it came to quality of life.
I'd rip that cord right outta the wall.

303
00:17:15.243 --> 00:17:16.244
Thanks. honey.

304
00:17:16.954 --> 00:17:19.998
You know you don't
literally pull the plug. right?

305
00:17:20.082 --> 00:17:21.834
You just make the call.

306
00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:23.085
That's less enticing.

307
00:17:23.167 --> 00:17:25.796
[Marley] Trust me.
you can wear it in his honor.

308
00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:29.383
I've been researching
some of that antiaging stuff.

309
00:17:29.466 --> 00:17:31.385
Testosterone. HGH.

310
00:17:31.969 --> 00:17:33.720
[Lisa] I mean.
it's not as out there as people think.

311
00:17:33.804 --> 00:17:35.806
I've been getting
vampire facials for years.

312
00:17:35.889 --> 00:17:39.268
Vitamins. hormones. stem cell infusions.

313
00:17:39.351 --> 00:17:41.478
[chuckles] Hey. you better believe.

314
00:17:41.562 --> 00:17:44.314
I'll be talking my kids into pumping
their blood into my veins.

315
00:17:44.398 --> 00:17:45.607
Why not. right?

316
00:17:46.984 --> 00:17:48.902
Are you and Hunter the same blood type?

317
00:17:49.903 --> 00:17:51.154
You should find out.

318
00:17:51.780 --> 00:17:53.115
You should.

319
00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:56.118
Diane had our plots picked out years ago.

320
00:17:56.201 --> 00:17:58.078
Yeah. of course I did.

321
00:17:58.161 --> 00:17:59.955
All the good spots get snapped up.

322
00:18:00.038 --> 00:18:03.083
If I left it to him. we'd be buried
on opposite sides of the cemetery.

323
00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:04.418
[chuckles]

324
00:18:04.501 --> 00:18:07.045
[chuckles] That's why
they call it resting in peace.

325
00:18:09.548 --> 00:18:12.050
[grunts. sips]

326
00:18:13.594 --> 00:18:15.470
[sighs] Let's see here.

327
00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:18.807
[Gretchen] You have to start taking
this stuff seriously. Coop.

328
00:18:18.891 --> 00:18:20.350
Heart disease runs in families.

329
00:18:20.434 --> 00:18:21.643
You're reaching that age. man.

330
00:18:21.727 --> 00:18:23.979
And it's not like you've had
a stress-free life.

331
00:18:24.062 --> 00:18:26.648
Finance guys keel over
at their desks all the time.

332
00:18:26.732 --> 00:18:28.984
It's a thing. Remember Johnny Arruda?

333
00:18:29.067 --> 00:18:31.153
- I think they would fit you perfectly.
- [Gretchen] He was fit.

334
00:18:31.236 --> 00:18:33.530
- Ran marathons. CrossFit. everything.
- [guest] Uh. sure. thank you.

335
00:18:33.614 --> 00:18:36.825
[Ashe] Learned everything I know from him.
But. uh… [blows] Yeah.

336
00:18:36.909 --> 00:18:40.078
My dad was a bull in a china shop
everywhere he went.

337
00:18:40.579 --> 00:18:43.081
This one time.
he noticed inventory was light. right?

338
00:18:43.165 --> 00:18:45.417
So. he goes and checks into it.
figures it's a port-level issue.

339
00:18:45.501 --> 00:18:47.753
So. he takes himself
all the way to Brooklyn Piers

340
00:18:47.836 --> 00:18:50.756
in the middle of winter.
asks his guys what's going on. right?

341
00:18:50.839 --> 00:18:52.341
No one's talking. okay?

342
00:18:52.424 --> 00:18:55.010
So. he elbows his way
onto this massive freighter.

343
00:18:55.093 --> 00:18:56.678
I'm talking about one of those huge ships.

344
00:18:56.762 --> 00:19:00.015
Irina Class. 1.300 feet.
propellers like the size of your house.

345
00:19:00.599 --> 00:19:03.936
Now. the guys start getting antsy because.
you know. they got a schedule to keep.

346
00:19:04.019 --> 00:19:05.479
And this really pisses him off.

347
00:19:05.562 --> 00:19:10.067
So. he-he storms into the bridge.
starts messing with the controls. right?

348
00:19:10.150 --> 00:19:13.445
Trying to cut the engines. which I guess
is some sort of union violation.

349
00:19:13.529 --> 00:19:17.991
because this huge Longshoremen's
Association motherfucker comes after him.

350
00:19:18.075 --> 00:19:19.284
says. "You can't touch shit."

351
00:19:19.368 --> 00:19:21.578
My dad gets in his face. yells at him.

352
00:19:21.662 --> 00:19:25.332
"These are my men. these are my goods.
I'll touch whatever the fuck I want."

353
00:19:26.166 --> 00:19:28.460
Somebody throws the first punch.

354
00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:30.170
They get into it.

355
00:19:30.254 --> 00:19:33.090
Long story short.
they both fall overboard.

356
00:19:33.674 --> 00:19:36.009
Yeah. 80-foot drop into the river

357
00:19:36.093 --> 00:19:39.179
and then… [exhales sharply]
…right under the hull.

358
00:19:39.888 --> 00:19:41.515
Jesus. that's a horrible way to die.

359
00:19:42.015 --> 00:19:44.560
Oh. no. My dad died at 78.

360
00:19:44.643 --> 00:19:46.061
Stage four. colon cancer.

361
00:19:46.645 --> 00:19:47.896
What are you gonna do?

362
00:19:52.776 --> 00:19:55.279
[Ali] My Annie Lennox is missing. Fuck!

363
00:19:55.362 --> 00:19:57.281
Oh. no. wait. Here it is. [chuckles]

364
00:20:02.828 --> 00:20:05.080
- This tastes stale.
- It's organic.

365
00:20:06.582 --> 00:20:09.042
The only reason I'm doing this
is 'cause you're mad at me.

366
00:20:10.878 --> 00:20:13.255
And. you know. death.

367
00:20:17.217 --> 00:20:19.219
- "It is decidedly so."
- [exhales sharply]

368
00:20:20.053 --> 00:20:21.054
[phone chimes]

369
00:20:23.223 --> 00:20:24.558
Goddamn it.

370
00:20:24.641 --> 00:20:26.935
- What?
- This goddamn dog.

371
00:20:27.019 --> 00:20:28.145
Wait. let me see.

372
00:20:28.896 --> 00:20:30.647
Oh. Hi. buddy.

373
00:20:30.731 --> 00:20:33.317
- Oh. are you a good boy?
- He's not a good boy.

374
00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:35.611
He takes giant dumps on my lawn.

375
00:20:36.862 --> 00:20:39.198
God. I've told these people
a million times.

376
00:20:39.281 --> 00:20:40.866
please keep your dog off our lawn.

377
00:20:40.949 --> 00:20:45.037
I don't think that's so much to ask.
to have your dog stay in your own yard?

378
00:20:45.537 --> 00:20:47.623
You should see these people.
they're so fucking condescending

379
00:20:47.706 --> 00:20:50.250
with their whole. like.
my-dog-is-my-child bullshit.

380
00:20:50.334 --> 00:20:54.087
Really. would you have your kid
shitting all over my lawn?

381
00:20:58.050 --> 00:20:59.051
What?

382
00:21:00.552 --> 00:21:01.678
Mom. you sound unhinged.

383
00:21:01.762 --> 00:21:03.931
I'm not unhinged. I'm totally hinged.

384
00:21:04.014 --> 00:21:05.224
- Mmm.
- Okay.

385
00:21:05.891 --> 00:21:08.685
- You're perseverating. [sighs]
- I regret teaching you that word.

386
00:21:08.769 --> 00:21:11.855
I move out. and you go full Nextdoor narc.

387
00:21:11.939 --> 00:21:13.607
Excuse me. how could I be a narc?

388
00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:15.692
I'm literally doing drugs
with my daughter.

389
00:21:15.776 --> 00:21:16.902
Is Mel a narc?

390
00:21:16.985 --> 00:21:18.195
[laughs]

391
00:21:19.696 --> 00:21:21.448
"Reply hazy. try again."

392
00:21:21.532 --> 00:21:23.575
- It knows we're high.
- Uh-huh.

393
00:21:26.578 --> 00:21:29.081
[sighs] You know what I need?

394
00:21:29.164 --> 00:21:30.415
- A job. [sighs]
- A fuck.

395
00:21:30.499 --> 00:21:32.501
- A life.
- Okay. wow. I was gonna say snacks.

396
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:34.378
Well. snacks are downstairs.

397
00:21:35.504 --> 00:21:37.673
- It's too far.
- Yeah. No. that's a nonstarter.

398
00:21:38.507 --> 00:21:41.510
["And Again" playing]

399
00:21:57.985 --> 00:21:59.027
[Hunter grunts]

400
00:22:00.445 --> 00:22:03.949
- Whoa. That's a first. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

401
00:22:04.032 --> 00:22:05.033
Help me up.

402
00:22:06.076 --> 00:22:07.661
[Delilah yelps. chuckles]

403
00:22:08.704 --> 00:22:11.123
[Ashe] Wow. It's such a beautiful photo.

404
00:22:11.206 --> 00:22:13.625
But look at you.
You look like a young Grace Kelly.

405
00:22:13.709 --> 00:22:14.793
Oh. shush.

406
00:22:14.877 --> 00:22:17.171
- I mean it. Spitting image. My gosh.
- Oh. stop.

407
00:22:17.254 --> 00:22:19.381
Bet you had to beat them away
with a stick. didn't you?

408
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:20.883
[both laughing]

409
00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:32.561
[Coop] Hey.

410
00:22:34.104 --> 00:22:35.772
These are from Bailey Russell?

411
00:22:35.856 --> 00:22:38.358
Why is Jack sending you flowers?

412
00:22:38.442 --> 00:22:41.236
- I'm doing a deal with him.
- With Jack? Are you kidding me?

413
00:22:41.320 --> 00:22:44.406
Well. I'm on the other side of the table.
It's completely different.

414
00:22:44.489 --> 00:22:46.742
The man screwed you.

415
00:22:48.035 --> 00:22:49.953
I'm sorry. are you high right now?

416
00:22:50.037 --> 00:22:52.497
What? [laughing]

417
00:22:52.581 --> 00:22:53.582
No.

418
00:22:54.333 --> 00:22:56.335
Well. okay. yes. But not like high high.

419
00:22:57.044 --> 00:22:58.295
Why? Am I acting weird?

420
00:22:58.962 --> 00:23:01.381
You know what? I don't care.

421
00:23:01.465 --> 00:23:04.218
I'm not gonna apologize
because your mother…

422
00:23:06.178 --> 00:23:07.971
- is a lot.
- Yeah. that she is.

423
00:23:08.055 --> 00:23:10.807
She is all that and a bag of chips.

424
00:23:11.391 --> 00:23:13.227
- What?
- [gasps] Do we have chips?

425
00:23:16.313 --> 00:23:17.856
What happened here. bub?

426
00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:20.442
- Nothing. I'm fine.
- Sweetheart. you are 16 years old.

427
00:23:20.526 --> 00:23:23.445
You have got to get better at lying to me.

428
00:23:24.112 --> 00:23:25.822
- He tripped.
- See? Like that.

429
00:23:30.994 --> 00:23:32.287
Is Grandma pissed at us?

430
00:23:32.371 --> 00:23:35.332
No. that's just her face
whenever I walk into a room.

431
00:23:35.415 --> 00:23:36.542
You get used to it.

432
00:23:38.001 --> 00:23:39.419
I'm not like that. am I?

433
00:23:39.503 --> 00:23:41.380
Don't sell yourself short. Mom.

434
00:23:44.842 --> 00:23:47.427
[exhales deeply]

435
00:23:58.647 --> 00:23:59.857
Where's the TV?

436
00:24:01.149 --> 00:24:02.693
Hey. Ho. What the fuck?

437
00:24:02.776 --> 00:24:04.319
Hello. where are you going?

438
00:24:04.403 --> 00:24:05.904
Wait. hold up. hold up. hold up.

439
00:24:06.572 --> 00:24:08.073
- What's wrong?
- What the fuck are you doing?

440
00:24:08.156 --> 00:24:10.492
Your mom asked us to take it down.
so we're bringing it to the garage.

441
00:24:10.576 --> 00:24:11.952
No. she was mistaken.

442
00:24:12.035 --> 00:24:14.204
Please. just… just put it back.

443
00:24:15.455 --> 00:24:16.540
Uh… [stammers]

444
00:24:16.623 --> 00:24:18.500
- Really? Jesus Christ.
- [Ashe] I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

445
00:24:18.584 --> 00:24:20.711
- Give me the goddamn TV.
- Your mom seemed really sure about it.

446
00:24:20.794 --> 00:24:22.796
She doesn't know
what the fuck she's talking about.

447
00:24:22.880 --> 00:24:24.923
And I don't even know
what the fuck you're doing here.

448
00:24:25.007 --> 00:24:27.134
- That's the grief talking.
- No. it isn't.

449
00:24:27.217 --> 00:24:29.511
Look. it was an honest mistake. I'm sorry.

450
00:24:30.012 --> 00:24:31.013
[Coop] Yeah. It's fine.

451
00:24:34.641 --> 00:24:35.893
Is that my dad's belt?

452
00:24:36.977 --> 00:24:40.230
Oh. yeah. Your mom gave it to me.
Said it looked nice with my suit.

453
00:24:40.314 --> 00:24:41.523
Wow.

454
00:24:43.150 --> 00:24:44.735
- [Ali] Andy.
- Where's Mom?

455
00:24:44.818 --> 00:24:47.070
I don't know. She's around here somewhere.
What did I miss?

456
00:24:47.154 --> 00:24:49.364
- Nothing. I just need to find her.
- I think you need to calm down.

457
00:24:49.448 --> 00:24:50.908
- I'm fine.
- No. you don't look fine.

458
00:24:50.991 --> 00:24:53.869
You look like you're about to
murder a widow with a flat screen.

459
00:24:53.952 --> 00:24:56.663
and believe me. nobody wants that
more than me. but not today.

460
00:24:56.747 --> 00:24:58.999
- Not today. Andy.
- Jesus. are you high too?

461
00:24:59.082 --> 00:25:00.709
Yeah. you want some?

462
00:25:00.792 --> 00:25:03.545
- It's s-stale but strong.
- No. thank you.

463
00:25:03.629 --> 00:25:05.130
Okay. well. you need to take a break.

464
00:25:05.214 --> 00:25:07.299
- What?
- Yeah. uh. tap out.

465
00:25:07.382 --> 00:25:10.385
Go to your room.
I'll handle down the fort down here.

466
00:25:10.469 --> 00:25:11.803
She's giving away his stuff.

467
00:25:11.887 --> 00:25:14.139
Well. she's a real bitch on wheels.
but what's new?

468
00:25:14.223 --> 00:25:15.807
- Ali… [exhales deeply]
- Go.

469
00:25:16.725 --> 00:25:18.060
[groans]

470
00:25:22.022 --> 00:25:23.023
[sighs]

471
00:25:26.902 --> 00:25:30.072
[sad music playing]

472
00:26:28.088 --> 00:26:30.007
[Coop narrating]
Cartier's Wax Seal Motif Cufflinks

473
00:26:30.090 --> 00:26:32.176
are designed to look like
the burnt insignias

474
00:26:32.259 --> 00:26:34.553
they used to seal letters with
back in the old days.

475
00:26:34.636 --> 00:26:37.222
This was before licking envelopes
and text messages.

476
00:26:37.306 --> 00:26:40.392
back when people still put periods
at the end of their sentences.

477
00:26:40.475 --> 00:26:43.312
The family seal told you
who the letter was from.

478
00:26:43.854 --> 00:26:48.025
It told the family who they were too.
or who they thought they were.

479
00:26:49.818 --> 00:26:51.778
Only a fool would give Cartier cuff links

480
00:26:51.862 --> 00:26:54.448
to a man who regularly shopped
the Brooks Brothers sale rack.

481
00:26:55.574 --> 00:26:58.577
I doubt Ron Cooper even had
a shirt that took cuff links.

482
00:26:58.660 --> 00:27:01.914
But it was his birthday.
and I wanted to give him something nice.

483
00:27:01.997 --> 00:27:05.375
So I went with a pair
of $4.800 designer cuff links

484
00:27:05.459 --> 00:27:07.586
that he. apparently.
never took out of the box.

485
00:27:08.670 --> 00:27:12.841
Like all gifts. this one said more
about the giver than the recipient.

486
00:27:13.592 --> 00:27:15.427
And I didn't love what it said about me.

487
00:27:47.167 --> 00:27:48.252
[Ali] No. How dare you?

488
00:27:48.335 --> 00:27:51.839
[Marley] I don't know why you have
to take everything so personally.

489
00:27:51.922 --> 00:27:54.007
I take it personally because
you're attacking my person!

490
00:27:54.091 --> 00:27:57.344
- What is going on here?
- I don't know. but we can't get out.

491
00:27:57.427 --> 00:27:59.763
- What happened there?
- Nothing. I'm fine.

492
00:27:59.847 --> 00:28:02.266
Hey. Mel. This is exactly like
what we were talking about upstairs.

493
00:28:02.349 --> 00:28:04.768
- You were talking about me?
- Of course not.

494
00:28:04.852 --> 00:28:07.271
- What's all this then?
- Just tell her what you told me.

495
00:28:07.354 --> 00:28:10.482
You know what? This is a family matter.
I just don't think I should get involved.

496
00:28:10.566 --> 00:28:12.025
No. you should not.

497
00:28:12.109 --> 00:28:14.152
- Mom.
- What? She's not family anymore.

498
00:28:14.236 --> 00:28:15.362
- Oh. okay.
- [Ali scoffs]

499
00:28:15.445 --> 00:28:17.948
Wow. Okay. can we all just dial
the temperature down a little bit?

500
00:28:18.031 --> 00:28:19.741
I have been biting my tongue
all goddamn day.

501
00:28:19.825 --> 00:28:21.451
and she just keeps poking at me.

502
00:28:21.535 --> 00:28:23.620
She pokes. It's a poke. a poke. a poke.

503
00:28:23.704 --> 00:28:26.373
It's like she wants me to go off
so she can poke me about that.

504
00:28:26.456 --> 00:28:28.876
I don't know what you're talking about.
My husband just died.

505
00:28:28.959 --> 00:28:30.627
- [Coop] Okay. Ali. Ali. Ali.
- Oh. [blows raspberry]

506
00:28:30.711 --> 00:28:32.379
- I think you need to tap out. okay?
- Me?

507
00:28:32.462 --> 00:28:34.631
Why don't you go to your room.
take a deep breath. calm down and--

508
00:28:34.715 --> 00:28:38.385
Coop. She's a grown woman.
You can't send her to her room.

509
00:28:38.468 --> 00:28:40.220
I thought you said
you weren't getting involved.

510
00:28:40.304 --> 00:28:41.388
I say a lot of things.

511
00:28:41.471 --> 00:28:43.056
Hold on!

512
00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:45.267
What in the sweet fuck are you doing here?

513
00:28:45.350 --> 00:28:46.810
[stammers] Your mom invited us.

514
00:28:46.894 --> 00:28:50.731
[scoffs] And you thought
it would be a good idea to come?

515
00:28:50.814 --> 00:28:52.441
[Bruce] I assumed she cleared it with you.

516
00:28:52.524 --> 00:28:53.734
No. she did not!

517
00:28:53.817 --> 00:28:55.110
[sighs]

518
00:28:55.194 --> 00:28:57.029
I'm really sorry about Ron.
He was a good man.

519
00:28:57.112 --> 00:28:59.781
Oh. thanks. Bruce.
Now. why don't you just go fuck off?

520
00:28:59.865 --> 00:29:01.408
- Hi. Joan.
- Allison.

521
00:29:01.491 --> 00:29:03.911
God. I cannot believe
you would fucking invite him.

522
00:29:03.994 --> 00:29:06.872
It's ancient history.
I just assumed we had all moved on.

523
00:29:06.955 --> 00:29:08.207
Bruce certainly has.

524
00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:11.543
Oh. if he had moved on.
he wouldn't have fucked me last year. huh?

525
00:29:11.627 --> 00:29:13.003
- [guests gasping]
- Damn it. Ali.

526
00:29:13.086 --> 00:29:15.506
Wait. wait. This is that Bruce?
Like. "Fuck Bruce" Bruce?

527
00:29:15.589 --> 00:29:17.132
Ali. I thought he'd be way hotter.

528
00:29:17.216 --> 00:29:19.092
- Ali…
- Tori. Excuse her. she's high.

529
00:29:19.176 --> 00:29:21.386
What? [stammers]
You're getting high with the children now?

530
00:29:21.470 --> 00:29:22.888
We had a breakthrough.

531
00:29:22.971 --> 00:29:24.264
- [Coop] Oh. my God. Really?
- Yeah.

532
00:29:24.348 --> 00:29:25.766
[Bruce] I think we should probably leave.

533
00:29:25.849 --> 00:29:27.142
Yes. I-I think so too.

534
00:29:27.226 --> 00:29:28.519
[Marley] Nonsense.

535
00:29:28.602 --> 00:29:29.978
You just got here.

536
00:29:30.062 --> 00:29:32.189
Are you fucking kidding me?

537
00:29:32.272 --> 00:29:34.983
- Joan is my friend.
- [Coop] Okay. New… New plan.

538
00:29:35.067 --> 00:29:36.443
New plan. Joan. please stay.

539
00:29:36.527 --> 00:29:38.153
Bruce. kindly fuck off.

540
00:29:38.237 --> 00:29:39.696
- I'm her ride.
- I swear to God. Bruce.

541
00:29:39.780 --> 00:29:40.781
[Bruce] Okay.

542
00:29:41.281 --> 00:29:43.158
[Grace retches]

543
00:29:43.242 --> 00:29:45.577
[guests gasping]

544
00:29:45.661 --> 00:29:47.496
- [Grace continues retching]
- [Barney] Oh. God. Oh.

545
00:29:47.579 --> 00:29:51.333
- Get my hair. get my hair. Barney.
- Oh. I got it. I got it. You're okay.

546
00:29:51.416 --> 00:29:53.710
Oh. my God. I'm so. so sorry.

547
00:29:53.794 --> 00:29:55.879
- Can I get some water?
- Yeah. I got it.

548
00:29:55.963 --> 00:29:59.007
[clamoring continues]

549
00:29:59.091 --> 00:30:00.801
[Grace] Oh. God.

550
00:30:00.884 --> 00:30:02.886
Oh. I'm so sorry.

551
00:30:04.888 --> 00:30:05.973
I'm so sorry.

552
00:30:08.350 --> 00:30:09.852
["Things Behind Things
Behind Things" playing]

553
00:30:09.935 --> 00:30:12.312
♪ I would like the feeling ♪

554
00:30:12.396 --> 00:30:15.190
♪ I would like the feeling ♪

555
00:30:15.274 --> 00:30:19.194
♪ I would like the feeling gone ♪

556
00:30:21.405 --> 00:30:24.491
♪ 'Cause I don't like the way it's ♪

557
00:30:24.575 --> 00:30:27.536
♪ I don't like the way it's ♪

558
00:30:27.619 --> 00:30:31.248
♪ I don't like the way it's looking ♪

559
00:30:32.958 --> 00:30:33.959
[sniffles]

560
00:30:34.042 --> 00:30:37.921
♪ I get caught looking in the mirror
On the regular ♪

561
00:30:39.214 --> 00:30:43.844
♪ What I see there resembles
Some competitor ♪

562
00:30:45.304 --> 00:30:49.766
♪ I see things behind things
Behind things ♪

563
00:30:51.351 --> 00:30:56.273
♪ And there are rings within rings
Within rings ♪

564
00:31:00.235 --> 00:31:01.486
[song continues]

565
00:31:18.879 --> 00:31:20.881
[song fades]

566
00:31:20.964 --> 00:31:23.175
[alt rock music playing]

567
00:31:30.557 --> 00:31:31.808
[clerk] What can I get ya?

568
00:31:31.892 --> 00:31:33.810
- Size 12. please.
- Got it.

569
00:31:37.648 --> 00:31:38.649
Okay.

570
00:32:11.473 --> 00:32:13.809
Hi. Sorry. you were at the cemetery.

571
00:32:13.892 --> 00:32:15.477
[chuckles] Elaine Naft.

572
00:32:15.561 --> 00:32:18.063
- Hi. Uh. Andrew Cooper.
- I know.

573
00:32:19.106 --> 00:32:20.440
Do you want to sit down?

574
00:32:21.441 --> 00:32:23.610
Uh. sure. Yes. I'd love to.

575
00:32:24.236 --> 00:32:25.320
[chuckles]

576
00:32:26.530 --> 00:32:27.531
[grunts]

577
00:32:29.825 --> 00:32:31.702
So. how did you know my dad?

578
00:32:31.785 --> 00:32:34.705
- We were on a bowling team together.
- Huh.

579
00:32:34.788 --> 00:32:38.417
We met every Thursday
for the past ten years.

580
00:32:39.042 --> 00:32:42.212
I… I thought the bowling team
disbanded years ago.

581
00:32:43.088 --> 00:32:45.090
We didn't let that stop us.

582
00:32:46.717 --> 00:32:47.718
Oh.

583
00:32:49.469 --> 00:32:51.680
I see. So. you. uh…

584
00:32:54.725 --> 00:32:56.101
Does that shock you?

585
00:32:58.854 --> 00:33:01.607
- He was a pretty straitlaced guy.
- [chuckles] He was.

586
00:33:02.608 --> 00:33:04.443
He was also a lot of other things.

587
00:33:05.611 --> 00:33:06.945
Is that so?

588
00:33:07.654 --> 00:33:08.655
[chuckles]

589
00:33:12.367 --> 00:33:13.702
He loved you very much.

590
00:33:14.828 --> 00:33:16.205
I'm sure you know that.

591
00:33:16.288 --> 00:33:17.289
Yeah.

592
00:33:19.666 --> 00:33:21.543
He talked about you a lot.

593
00:33:21.627 --> 00:33:23.170
You and your sister.

594
00:33:25.422 --> 00:33:26.840
That's funny.
He never mentioned you at all.

595
00:33:26.924 --> 00:33:28.509
[chuckles]

596
00:33:28.592 --> 00:33:30.636
No. I don't suppose he would've.

597
00:33:32.596 --> 00:33:35.390
So. what was the plan? You guys were
gonna run off together or something?

598
00:33:35.474 --> 00:33:38.227
God. no. We were both too old for that.

599
00:33:40.270 --> 00:33:41.563
I think we were…

600
00:33:43.482 --> 00:33:45.484
just lonely in the same way.

601
00:33:47.694 --> 00:33:49.029
And having each other…

602
00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:53.200
well. it made things better.

603
00:33:55.536 --> 00:33:57.663
Is it weird that it makes me
happy to hear that?

604
00:34:03.126 --> 00:34:05.045
Honestly. I thought we'd have more time.

605
00:34:06.380 --> 00:34:07.381
Yeah.

606
00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:09.216
You and me both.

607
00:34:11.176 --> 00:34:12.969
He worried about you. you know?

608
00:34:13.053 --> 00:34:15.889
[stammers]
Well. I got into some trouble last year.

609
00:34:15.973 --> 00:34:18.475
but I'm… It's all sorted out.

610
00:34:18.559 --> 00:34:20.561
No. he worried about you before that.

611
00:34:21.143 --> 00:34:23.480
He worried you might never be happy.

612
00:34:27.693 --> 00:34:28.694
Is anyone?

613
00:34:29.360 --> 00:34:31.154
I'd like to think he was.

614
00:34:31.237 --> 00:34:34.116
Yeah. I don't know.
He took a lot of shit at home and at work.

615
00:34:35.784 --> 00:34:38.161
I think sometimes
it felt like he had just given up.

616
00:34:38.829 --> 00:34:39.830
[chuckles]

617
00:34:41.123 --> 00:34:42.291
Is that funny?

618
00:34:44.168 --> 00:34:46.128
You're exactly like he said.

619
00:34:46.210 --> 00:34:47.212
What do you mean?

620
00:34:47.963 --> 00:34:49.715
You're angry at the world.

621
00:34:50.632 --> 00:34:52.426
Yeah. The world can be a shitty place.

622
00:34:53.177 --> 00:34:54.469
Maybe.

623
00:34:55.179 --> 00:34:58.140
Maybe there's something in you
that expects too much out of it.

624
00:34:58.849 --> 00:35:00.559
So. I should just settle for less?

625
00:35:02.144 --> 00:35:03.228
Like he did.

626
00:35:03.812 --> 00:35:05.147
You think he settled?

627
00:35:05.898 --> 00:35:07.357
I think he deserved more.

628
00:35:16.825 --> 00:35:19.286
Ron's life might've looked small to you.

629
00:35:19.369 --> 00:35:22.831
but the way he saw it.
he had his whole world under one roof.

630
00:35:25.334 --> 00:35:26.919
That made him happy.

631
00:35:33.300 --> 00:35:34.927
I already miss him.

632
00:35:40.724 --> 00:35:42.142
You and me both. honey.

633
00:35:42.226 --> 00:35:43.977
[inhales sharply. sighs]

634
00:35:47.356 --> 00:35:49.733
You really believe that?
That he was happy?

635
00:35:50.526 --> 00:35:52.611
I think he was happy by nature. [chuckles]

636
00:35:53.320 --> 00:35:55.864
I think he found things to be happy about.

637
00:35:57.491 --> 00:36:01.411
And for everything else.
there was bowling.

638
00:36:05.082 --> 00:36:06.083
[sighing] Yeah.

639
00:36:14.675 --> 00:36:15.968
[exhales deeply]

640
00:36:28.689 --> 00:36:31.316
[inhales deeply. sighs]

641
00:36:34.069 --> 00:36:38.073
[breathes deeply]

642
00:36:45.581 --> 00:36:46.665
[sniffles]

643
00:37:07.978 --> 00:37:09.313
[sniffles]

644
00:37:20.324 --> 00:37:21.325
[chuckles]

645
00:37:24.661 --> 00:37:25.954
[sniffles]

646
00:37:46.099 --> 00:37:48.101
["Keep Me In Your Heart" plays on radio]

647
00:38:03.534 --> 00:38:04.993
- [Tori] Mom in here?
- Yep.

648
00:38:05.077 --> 00:38:06.078
Come on.

649
00:38:06.161 --> 00:38:07.162
- Bye.
- Bye.

650
00:38:08.121 --> 00:38:09.122
[Delilah] Bye.

651
00:38:37.359 --> 00:38:39.194
[Marley crying]

652
00:39:40.589 --> 00:39:43.842
[beeping]

653
00:40:05.989 --> 00:40:07.908
- Hello.
- [clerk] How many?

654
00:40:07.991 --> 00:40:12.871
Just three of us.
She's a size 3. he's a 9. I'm a 12.

655
00:40:31.473 --> 00:40:32.474
[bowling pins clatter]

656
00:40:36.103 --> 00:40:37.729
[songs ends]
